
[1]amorous

   AM'OROUS, a. [L. amor, love.]

   1. Inclined to love; having a propensity to love, or to sexual
   enjoyment; loving; fond.

   2. In love; enamored.

   3. Pertaining or relating to love; produced by love; indicating love;
   as amorous delight; amorous airs.
